CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1781806274
OL,3,CStrep B campaigner hopeful of
OL,4,Cbreakthrough in national testing
OL,6,FIt comes as clinical trials of Group B
OL,7,FStrep testing have been taking place
OL,8,Fin maternity units at more than 70 NHS
OL,9,FTrusts, including a number from within
OL,10,Fthe Meridian region.
OL,12,FResults from the trials are expected
OL,13,Fin the Autumn at a time where the
OL,14,Fgovernment is trying to raise the
OL,15,Fstandard of care given to pregnant
OL,16,Fwomen.
OL,18,FGroup B Strep, if passed onto babies
OL,19,Fduring pregnancy, can lead to serious
OL,20,Fillnesses, including Sepsis, Pneumonia
OL,21,Fand Meningitis.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
